summary:
Online Portfolio: https://issuu.com/camilacaiza/docs/a4_single_page_complete_portfolio_2
WebSite: http://www.camilacaiza.com/

Ecuadorian Architecht, Scenographer and Designer based in Amersfoort, the Netherlands. 

Exploring the qualities and relationships of space during my architectural studies lead me to discover my interest in how space can become a reflection of a narrative, but also a reflection of life and the human nature itself. With this in mind, and also pursuing an urge to combine the skills required to design a space in architecture with the sensibility of performative arts, I decided to connect my architectural studies with an artistic perspective on space. Therefore, I started the Master in Scenography at the HKU (Hogeschool voor de Kunsten Utrecht) which I completed in June 2017. 

As a result of this journey I experienced a relevant transformation, as a professional adding scenography to my architectural background, but also as an experience that changed me in a deeper level as a human being. It challenged me to try new things as building up real scale spaces or generating spatial installations with performative elements like lights, sound, narrative; etc., and most of all it has given me the chance to explore art from a personal point of view and to share it with other people. 

Therefore, my main interests still remain in the qualities and possibilities of space, both through an architectonic point of view, but also from a filmic - theatrical approach wich can lead to a performative experience.
